description: {"blocks":[{"key":"5gj71","text":"This protocol describes how to measure the rate of uptake of FFN102, a fluorescent DAT substrate inside midbrain dopaminergic neurons. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"131v","text":"To measure the presence and activity of the DAT, we utilised the commercially available fluorescent DAT and VMAT2 substrate FFN102 (Abcam, ab120866). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dt715","text":"To measure the uptake of the FFN102 dye, a field of view was first found using the brightfield settings on a Zeiss LSM 880 confocal microscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3drfi","text":"Cells were washed 1x with HBSS at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmpr","text":"The cells then had 10 μM of the FFN102 dye in HBSS added and a time-series with an exposure every 5 seconds using the 405 nm laser was started, to measure uptake of the dye into the cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fm0a1","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2isdq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ndej","text":"Excited using the 405 nm laser line and emission between 405 nm to 470 nm.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8hvua","text":"As a control to confirm specificity, samples in a different well were pre-treated with 5 μM of the DAT inhibitor nomifensine (Sigma) for 10 minutes in HBSS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"df6ea","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6trv","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"7iva0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"5bbur","text":"Nomifensine was kept in cell solution also after FFN102 was added.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eef96","text":"Once the dye had entered cells, the cells were depolarised by the addition of 50 mM KCl to observe FFN102 dynamics.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"epl4i","text":"Rate of fluorescence intensity increase inside cells was measured across the time-series to give a readout for the rate of FFN102 uptake through the dopamine transporter.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
